s. Opening timely new dialogues between the various fields of Jewish, feminist, queer, trans, decolonial, and critical race studies, Jewcy encourages readers both inside and outside the academy to rethink narrow conceptions of Jewishness.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 4aGender and Sexuality : Feminist. 4aGender and Sexuality : Lesbian / Gay Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Queer Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / LGBT Studies / Lesbian Studies.2bisacsh1 aBrettschneider, Marla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrettschneider, Marla, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConaway, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHakimi, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHakkâri, A. S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLadin, Joy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLev, Sarra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatlow, Rona B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrell, Vinny Calvo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShimonov, Ruben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSojourner, Sabrina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStein, Leonard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTawil, Marielle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2024z978311149259940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849628340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438496283423Coveruhttps://www.d